div.p: RUNGS, in a ſhip, the ſame with the floor or ground timbers ; being the timbers which conftitute her floor ; and are bolted to the keel, whoſe ends are rung-heads.
Rung-Heads, in a ſhip, are made a little bending to direct the sweep or mold of the futtocks and navel-timbers ; for here the lines begin which make the compaſs and bearing of the ſhip.
